        <div n="Z773570B" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">by Archdeacon Walls</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-1"> Six Holland shirts, six night-caps with borders&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-2"> Bespoke, &amp; made up according to orders:</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-3"> A Night-Gown refresh'd, well scower'd &amp; clean,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-4"> New-facings &amp; robings, you know what I mean:</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-5"> A Scarf of black Silk, some call it a Tippet,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-6"> With wick at y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> End, you may hem it or whip it:</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-7"> Twelve China plates of pure white &amp; blue:</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-8"> Three Shirts for a blackguard, all spik-span &amp; new;</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-9"> A Debt of long-standing, which no one doth think of:</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-10"> My poor dear Neddy hath gotten y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> Chincough.</l></lg><lg n="2" type="stanza"><l n="11" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-11">Answer'd, by Cap<hi rend="sup">t</hi>: Knypes.</l></lg><lg n="3" type="stanza"><l n="12" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-12">'Tis many an honest Trader's fate&#13;</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-13"> Whole Years for payment of his debts to wait.</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-14"> Full of't must he whine out a mournful Dun,</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-15"> Whilst y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> gay debtor, plays in joke or pun;</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-16"> Daggled in Dirt becomes y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> great man's Scoff,</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-17"> Waiting at door produces y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> Chincough.</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-18"> Would you avoid a treatment thus gallant,</l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-19"> No more of Shirts or Nightcaps do you taunt.</l><l n="20" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-20"> What, if you furbisht out a page blackguard?</l><l n="21" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-21"> Virtue, say Preachers, is it's own Reward.</l><l n="22" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-22"> Dream not of payment, or in part or whole;</l><l n="23" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-23"> Think of y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> Yards of Holland you have stole.</l><l n="24" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-24"> To ease your Conscience, learn to weep &amp; pray,</l><l n="25" xml:id="spp-Z773570B-line-25"> Your Rhimes shall never lure my pence away.Z773570B   </l></lg></div>
